      "name": "Vialone-Nano rice",
      "amount": "250g"
    },
    {
      "name": "Pumpkin",
      "amount": "500g"
    },
    {
      "name": "Red sweet potato",
      "amount": "500g"
    },
    {
      "name": "Chicken broth",
      "amount": "2L"
    },
    {
      "name": "Coconut milk",
      "amount": "250ml"
    },
    {
      "name": "Lemon juice",
      "amount": "2 tbsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "Fresh parsley",
      "amount": "1/4 cup"
    },
    {
      "name": "Salt",
      "amount": "1 tsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "Black pepper",
      "amount": "1 tsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "Spinach",
      "amount": "100g"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Combine Vialone-Nano rice, pumpkin, and red sweet potato in a pressure cooker. ",
    "Add chicken broth, coconut milk, lemon juice, salt, and black pepper to the pressure cooker. ",
    "Close the lid and cook at 15 psi for 30 minutes. ",
    "Quick-release the pressure and carefully remove the lid. ",
    "Stir in fresh parsley and cook for an additional 2 minutes. ",
    "Add spinach and cook until wilted. ",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired. ",
    "Reserve leftover stew for up to 3 days in the refrigerator. "
  ],
